  "market_context": "NQ was in a consolidation range with equal highs and a swept low (three drives into previous day low). Price failed to displace out of the range, setting up a potential trade back into the previous day's range at the 10:00 a.m. new hourly/4-hour candle.",
  "key_observation": "The 10:00 a.m. new 4-hour candle closure provided HTF confirmation, with the 5-minute structure already aligned and a t-spot zone marking where the higher time frame wick was anticipated to form, enabling a precise 1-minute inversion entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified the consolidation range with equal highs and swept lows (three drives into previous day low), noting price kept failing to displace lower.",
    "Anticipated a move back into the previous day's range at the 10:00 a.m. new hourly/4-hour candle.",
    "Waited for the 1-hour closure and dropped down to the 5-minute time frame to confirm alignment.",
    "Observed the indicator's t-spot zone where the higher time frame wick was expected to form.",
    "Dropped to the 1-minute time frame and waited for a sweep of a prior low plus an inversion within the t-spot area.",
    "Confirmed price swept the low to the left and formed an inversion, then waited for a close over the inversion.",
    "Took entry on the retest of the inversion with stop on the low, targeting 2R."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade tagged in, briefly missed initial TP, then hit the 2R take profit target.",
  "lessons": "Aligning the 1-hour closure with the 5-minute t-spot zone and a 1-minute inversion entry produces a high-probability setup. The 10:00–11:00 window provides time-based expansion, and retest entries near short-term highs help secure profits before exhaustion.",
